  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "50 \u0b86\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc6\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bca\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc8 \u0b87\u0bb1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd\u0baf \u0ba8\u0b9f\u0bb5\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 - \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bcb",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Action to import 50 thousand metric tons of rice - Minister Nalin Fernando",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "Even as the country is facing a crisis situation, the government has taken all measures to provide essential commodities to the people without shortage.",
        "Trade and Food Security Minister Nalin Fernando said that steps have been taken to purchase 50,000 metric tons of rice through the commercial association.",
        "He said this in the parliament on Wednesday (6) in reference to the decision of the Ministry of Commerce.",
        "Adequate measures have been taken to provide essential goods without shortage through 444 SQM outlets nationwide.",
        "For that purpose, steps have been taken to procure 50,000 metric tons of rice through a business association. A large number of essential commodities are available to the country in the coming weeks.",
        "With the help of the World Bank and the World Food Program and the Government of India, we have taken steps to purchase essential commodities. Although there is a ban on the export of sugar and wheat flour in India, the negotiations regarding the import of sugar and wheat flour from India have been completed.",
        "The Government of India has decided to supply essential commodities worth USD 180 million to Sri Lanka and the essential commodities will be available to the country in the next two months. The work plan to provide essential goods to the general public without shortage is being carried out as a joint work plan of the government and private sector.",
        "Steps have been taken to import essential food items and supply them to people at low prices. A work plan is being carried out to procure all food items through requisition. Accordingly, steps will be taken to import fifteen important essential food items and get them to consumers at low prices.",
        "At the same time, special laws will be brought against those who collect and hoard essential food items and legal action will be taken against them. Negotiations are being held with the Attorney General in this regard.",
        "A price control has been imposed on rice and currently Natari is selling at Rs 220 per kg, Samba rice at Rs 230 per kg and Keersamba at Rs 260 per kg. He said that steps will be taken to procure other essential items at controlled prices in the future"
      ],
